parameters: The Kingdom of heaven is like this. Once there
was a man who went out early in the morning to
hire some men to work in his vineyard.
El reino de los cielos se puede comparar
al dueño de una finca que salió muy de mañana
a contratar trabajadores para su viña.
Perquè amb el Regne del cel passa com amb un
propietari que va sortir de bon matí a llogar
treballadors per a la seva vinya.
He agreed to pay them the regular wage,
a silver coin a day, and sent them to work
Acordó con ellos pagarles el salario de un día
y los mandó a trabajar a su viña.
Després de fer tractes amb ells per un jornal
d'un denari, els envià a la seva propietat.
He went out again to the marketplace at nine
o'clock and saw some men standing there doing
Volvió a salir sobre las nueve de la mañana
y vio a otros que estaban en la plaza,
Va tornar a sortir cap a mig matí,
You also go and work in the vineyard,
and I will pay you a fair wage.
Id también vosotros a trabajar a mi viña.
Os daré lo que sea justo.
Aneu també vosaltres a la meva vinya
i us donaré el que sigui just.
Then at twelve o'clock and again at three
o'clock he did the same thing. It was nearly
five o'clock when he went to the marketplace
and saw some other men still standing there.
El dueño salió de nuevo hacia el mediodía, y
otra vez a las tres de la tarde, hizo lo mismo.
Alrededor de las cinco de la tarde volvió a la
plaza y encontró a otros desocupados.

Well, then, you go and work in the vineyard.
¿Por qué estáis aquí todo el día, sin trabajar?
Id también vosotros a trabajar a mi viña.
Per què us esteu aquí tot el dia sense fer res?
És que ningú no ens ha llogat.
Aneu també vosaltres a la meva vinya.
When evening came, the owner told his foreman:
Call the workers and pay them their wages,
starting with those who were hired last
and ending with those who were hired first.
The men who had begun to work at five o'clock
were paid a silver coin each.
So when the men who were the first to be hired
came to be paid, they thought they would get
more; but they too were given a silver coin
They took their money and started grumbling
These men who were hired last worked only one
hour, while we put up with a whole day's work
in the hot sun—yet you paid them the same as
The owner answered one of them:
Listen, friend, I have not cheated you.
After all, you agreed to do a day's work for
one silver coin. Now take your pay and go home.
I want to give this man who was hired last as
much as I gave you. Don't I have the right to
do as I wish with my own money?
Or are you jealous because I am generous?
So those who are last will be first, and those
who are first will be last.
and Jesus went to his house.

Quan va tocar als primers, es pensaven que
cobrarien més, però també van rebre un denari.
Aquests darrers han treballat només una hora i
els pagues igual que a nosaltres, que hem hagut
de suportar el pes de la jornada i la calor.
L'amo va respondre a un d'aquests:
Company, jo no et faig cap injustícia.
¿No havíem fet tractes per un denari? Doncs
pren el que és teu i vés-te'n.
A aquest darrer li vull donar igual que a tu.
¿Que no puc fer el que vull amb el que és meu?
¿O és que tens enveja perquè jo sóc generós?
Així, els darrers passaran a primers,
and Jesus went to his house.
